title: High school sports roundup
text:
Hartley 3, Highland 2 
Highland lost its first match of the season Monday in a matchup of state-ranked teams. 
The Lady Scots, ranked fourth in Ohio in Division III, fell to Hartley, the 18th-rated squad in Div. II, by scores of 28-30, 25-23, 17-25, 25-22, 7-15. 
Brogin Denman swatted 15 kills and had 21 digs for Highland (18-1). Elora Stiltner added 14 kills and four blocks; Ashton Terrill had 10 kills and 25 digs; Bridget Oder produced 36 digs; Jorden Goodman had 15 assists; and Taylor Belcher added 18 assists.
